  "method": [
    "Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. Crosshatch bread",
    "using a serrated knife, cutting slices every inch in both",
    "directions but not through the bottom of the baguette.",
    "Combine melted butter, garlic, and parsley in a small bowl—",
    "Salt & pepper to taste.",
    "Brush the melted butter mixture within the crosshatches of the",
    "baguette.",
    "Stuff mozzarella and fontina into each crosshatch and wrap the",
    "bread in foil thoroughly.",
    "Baked for 20 minutes, or until the butter cheese has melted and",
    "the bread is toasty warm.",
    "Allow cooling for 5 minutes before serving."
  ],
